<item>
            <title>[LU-19895] implement large folio support</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19895</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This ticket is to track the semantics of how the large folios are implemented.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do they impose a minimum &quot;chunk&quot; size for read-modify-write?  Does the stripe_size of a file affect the folio size?  Or are the folios opportunistically sized (e.g. application read/write size up to the stripe size).   Should there be a &lt;tt&gt;llite.&amp;#42;.large_folio=N&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;KMG&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; tunable that allows specify the minimum folio size for the file, or possibly in the near future the compression chunk size should set this internally, so that the page cache handles the complexity of aggregating multiple pages into a chunk to avoid issues with mmap.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="95770">LU-19895</key>
            <summary>implement large folio support</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11310&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Improvement</type>
                                            <priority id="10104" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/priorities/medium.svg">Medium</priority>
                        <status id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/statuses/open.png" description="The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.">Open</status>
                    <statusCategory id="2" key="new" colorName="default"/>
